# ✊✋✌️ Day 4 - Rock Paper Scissors

This is a classic Rock, Paper, Scissors game built in Python as part of the **100 Days of Code** challenge.

The player competes against the computer by choosing rock, paper, or scissors. The winner is determined based on traditional game rules.

## 🚀 Features

- Randomized computer choice using the `random` module
- Player vs. computer gameplay
- Input validation and result display

## 🛠️ Built With

- Python 3

## 🧠 What I Practiced

- Using the `random` module
- Conditional logic
- Working with lists and user input

---

Part of the [100 Days of Code](https://github.com/Synel96/100-Days-Of-Code) journey.
